Aim:- To Demonstrate Various Data types & Operators in Python 

Algorithm:-

Step:1.	Start
Step:2. Initialize values for monthly income, rent, groceries, utilities, and luxury item cost.
Step:3. Calculate total expenses using total_expenses = rent + groceries + utilities.
Step:4.	Calculate monthly savings usingsavings = monthly_income − total_expenses.
Step:5.	Calculate annual savings and daily budget.
Step:6.	Calculate number of luxury items that can be bought and the remaining money.
Step:7.	Display total expenses, savings, annual savings, daily budget, number of luxury items, and leftover cash.
Step:8.	Stop.

Code:- #DATA TYPES AND OPERATORS 
monthly_income = 5000

rent = 1500
groceries = 600
utilities = 300
luxury_item_cost = 450

total_expenses = rent + groceries + utilities

savings = monthly_income - total_expenses

print("Total expenses: $", total_expenses)
print("Monthly savings: $", savings)

annual_savings = savings * 12

daily_budget = monthly_income / 30

print("Predicted annual savings: $", annual_savings)
print("Average daily budget: $", daily_budget)

num_items = savings 
leftover_cash = savings % luxury_item_cost

print("You can buy luxury items:", num_items)
print("Leftover pocket money after purchase: $", leftover_cash)


